# Fix: get_native_this() Bug

## Problem
`get_native_this()` used `Cell::take()` which removes and returns the value, setting the cell to `None`.
If `get_native_this()` is called multiple times in the same call chain (e.g., chained native function calls),
subsequent calls would get `None` instead of the original `this` value.

## Root Cause
```rust
// BEFORE (broken):
static CURRENT_THIS: Cell<Option<Value>> = const { Cell::new(None) };
pub fn get_native_this() -> Option<Value> {
    CURRENT_THIS.with(|cell| cell.take())  // ← take() consumes and clears the cell
}
```

`Cell::take()` requires `T: Copy`. Since `Option<Value>` is not `Copy` (Value is not Copy), we cannot use `cell.get().clone()` directly.

## Fix
Changed `CURRENT_THIS` from `Cell<Option<Value>>` to `RefCell<Option<Value>>`, which allows
borrowing without consuming:

```rust
// AFTER (fixed):
static CURRENT_THIS: RefCell<Option<Value>> = const { RefCell::new(None) };
pub fn get_native_this() -> Option<Value> {
    CURRENT_THIS.with(|cell| cell.borrow().clone())  // ← borrow() + clone(), non-consuming
}
```

Also updated `set_native_this` to use `cell.replace(...)` instead of `cell.set(...)`
(since `RefCell` doesn't have `set` the same way `Cell` does — `replace` is the idiomatic
`RefCell` equivalent that returns the old value).

## Files Changed
- `crates/quench-runtime/src/interpreter/mod.rs`

## Verification
- All 45 runtime tests pass: `cargo test -p quench-runtime`
- `cargo check` succeeds
